## 7. Exportación de Datos

### Exportar a Google Drive:
```javascript
// Imagen a Drive
Export.image.toDrive({
  image: classified,
  description: 'clasificacion_santiago',
  folder: 'EarthEngine',
  region: aoi,
  scale: 10,
  crs: 'EPSG:32719',
  maxPixels: 1e13
});

// Tabla a Drive
Export.table.toDrive({
  collection: featureCollection,
  description: 'datos_vectoriales',
  folder: 'EarthEngine',
  fileFormat: 'GeoJSON'  // o CSV, SHP, KML
});
```

### Exportar a Google Cloud Storage:
```javascript
Export.image.toCloudStorage({
  image: composite,
  description: 'composite_s2',
  bucket: 'mi-bucket-gcs',
  fileNamePrefix: 'composites/santiago_2024',
  region: aoi,
  scale: 10,
  crs: 'EPSG:32719',
  fileFormat: 'GeoTIFF'
});
```

### Exportar como Asset de Earth Engine:
```javascript
Export.image.toAsset({
  image: classified,
  description: 'clasificacion_asset',
  assetId: 'projects/mi-proyecto/assets/clasificacion_santiago',
  region: aoi,
  scale: 10,
  crs: 'EPSG:32719'
});
```

### Cloud Optimized GeoTIFF (COG):
```python
# Cargar COG directamente desde Cloud Storage
image = ee.Image.loadGeoTIFF('gs://mi-bucket/mi-imagen.tif')
```

